<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/spor/2007-05-09.1.4" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80272" speakername="The Presiding Officer (Mr George Reid)"  colnum="1" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/officialReports/meetingsParliament/or-07/sor0509-02.htm#Col1" time="09:30:00">
<p>The third session of the Scottish Parliament is now convened. I warmly welcome all new and returning members.</p>

<p>We proceed directly to members' oaths and affirmations. I will call each member in turn. When a member is called, they should proceed to the well of the chamber to take the oath or make an affirmation.</p>
</speech>

