<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/spor/2007-05-09.8.1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80272" speakername="The Presiding Officer (Mr George Reid)"  colnum="8" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/officialReports/meetingsParliament/or-07/sor0509-02.htm#Col8" time="12:06:00">
<p>I am now minded to take a motion without notice, that motion S3M-1, a copy of which has been placed on members' desks and which is supported by all parties in the chamber, be taken at this meeting of Parliament.</p>
</speech>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/spor/2007-05-09.8.2" nospeaker="true"  colnum="8" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/officialReports/meetingsParliament/or-07/sor0509-02.htm#Col8" time="12:06:00">
<p><em>
Motion moved,
</em></p>

<p>That motion S3M-1 be taken at this meeting of the Parliament.&#151;[
<em>
 Alasdair Morgan
</em>
.]</p>
</speech>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/spor/2007-05-09.8.3" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80272" speakername="The Presiding Officer"  colnum="8" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/officialReports/meetingsParliament/or-07/sor0509-02.htm#Col8" time="12:06:00">
<p>This is a two-step process. The first question is, that the motion without notice be agreed to. Are we agreed?</p>
</speech>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/spor/2007-05-09.8.4" nospeaker="true"  colnum="8" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/officialReports/meetingsParliament/or-07/sor0509-02.htm#Col8" time="12:06:00">
<p><em>
Motion agreed to.
</em></p>
</speech>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/spor/2007-05-09.8.5" nospeaker="true"  colnum="8" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/officialReports/meetingsParliament/or-07/sor0509-02.htm#Col8" time="12:06:00">
<p><em>
Motion moved,
</em></p>

<p>That the Parliament agrees that, for the purposes of electing a Presiding Officer and two Deputy Presiding Officers, the third sentence of Rule 8.16 of Standing Orders be suspended and that under Rule 8.16 thus varied, this meeting of the Parliament be adjourned until 3.00 pm on Monday 14 May 2007.&#151;[
<em>
 Alasdair Morgan.
</em>
]</p>
</speech>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/spor/2007-05-09.8.6" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80272" speakername="The Presiding Officer"  colnum="8" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/officialReports/meetingsParliament/or-07/sor0509-02.htm#Col8" time="12:06:00">
<p>The second question is, that motion S3M-1, on suspension of standing orders, to allow this meeting of Parliament to be adjourned, be agreed to. Are we agreed?</p>
</speech>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/spor/2007-05-09.8.7" nospeaker="true"  colnum="8" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/officialReports/meetingsParliament/or-07/sor0509-02.htm#Col8" time="12:06:00">
<p><em>
Motion agreed to.
</em></p>
</speech>

